According to the [[Book of Jubilees]], '''Awan''' (also '''Avan''' or '''Aven''', from [[Hebrew]] אָוֶן ''aven'' "vice", "iniquity", "potency") was the wife and sister of [[Cain]] and the daughter of [[Adam and Eve]].<ref>The Empowerment of Women in the Book of Jubilees - Page 17, Betsy Halpern Amaru - 1999</ref> Similarly, her sister [[Azura (religious figure)|Azura]] (עֲצֻרָה ''atzurah'' "restraint") was the wife of Cain's two brothers: [[Abel]] and after Abel's murder, [[Seth]]. In one Hebrew chronological work, she is called ''Balbira''.<ref name="Seder Hadorot">Seder Hadorot 8a</ref><ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=6uK5pa3R4d8C&pg=PA51&dq=Balbira+Abel Abarbanel Gen. 4,1 as cited by Codex Judaica]</ref>

