'''Theodidaktos''' ([[Ancient Greece|Greek]], from ''theos'' - 'god', and ''didaktos'' - taught) were "the immediate disciples of [[Ammonius Saccas]], who was called Theodidaktos, “God-Taught” – such as [[Plotinus]] and his follower [[Porphyry (philosopher)|Porphyry]]."<ref> Helena Blavatsky, "The Key To Theosophy" Theosophical Publishing Society., pages 2.</ref>
